I basically have no idea. The graph going back a few years seems to be on a positive up (to 4100 ish) and the recent month seems down on average. I looked at the forecasts from experts (and how they performed in recent months) on Trading Economics and they had a consensus of 4099. The consensus of our group here seems negative in comparison. We have a crunch event going on with Brexit in the EU which seems to be reaching a decision point. All sides are interested in making it good and nobody seems particular strong politically. So I've gone for a more positive spread.
Futures say 3978. Was 3984 today.
Unless there is a trigger event, there should not be much variation, given this is usually a quiet time of year for trading.

Trading Economics sees the BEL 20 at 4010 by end of Q4 before dipping further in 2018. I don’t think it has much room to run too much above 4,000 before 12/15. So I’m putting greater weight on the 3,985 to 4,065 bucket.
